      "*   To sustain and grow, we need to understand the underlying causes of those mid-year sales slowdowns and develop strategies to either mitigate them or capitalize on the factors driving our peak performance.\n",
      "*   There's a clear opportunity to refine our pricing and product strategies, potentially adapting to seasonal demand or market dynamics to maximize revenue throughout the year.\n",
      "*   By focusing on these insights, we can move from reactive reporting to proactive decision-making, optimizing sales efforts and resource allocation for future growth.\n",
      "\n",
      "## 2. Power BI / Fabric Report Blueprint\n",
      "\n",
      "### 2.1 Data Model & Tables\n",
      "\n",
      "The design would follow a Star Schema approach for optimal performance and analytical flexibility in Power BI.\n",
      "\n",
      "*   **Fact Table:** `Fact_Sales`\n",
      "    *   **Purpose:** Stores all transactional details.\n",
      "    *   **Columns:** `DateKey` (FK), `CustomerID` (FK), `ProductKey` (FK), `RegionKey` (FK), `ChannelKey` (FK), `Quantity`, `Discount`, `UnitPrice`, `SalesAmount`.\n",
      "    *   **Keys & Relationships:**\n",
      "        *   `DateKey` relates to `Dim_Date[DateKey]` (Many-to-One)\n",
      "        *   `CustomerID` relates to `Dim_Customer[CustomerID]` (Many-to-One)\n",
      "        *   `ProductKey` relates to `Dim_Product[ProductKey]` (Many-to-One)\n",
      "        *   `RegionKey` relates to `Dim_Region[RegionKey]` (Many-to-One)\n",
      "        *   `ChannelKey` relates to `Dim_Channel[ChannelKey]` (Many-to-One)\n",
      "\n",
      "*   **Dimension Tables:**\n",
      "\n",
      "    *   `Dim_Date`\n",
      "        *   **Purpose:** Provides rich date intelligence.\n",
      "        *   **Columns:** `DateKey` (PK, e.g., an integer `YYYYMMDD`), `FullDateAlternateKey` (original `Date` value), `Year`, `MonthNumber`, `MonthName`, `Quarter`, `DayOfWeek`, `DayName`, `IsWeekend`, etc.\n",
      "        *   **Key:** `DateKey`\n",
      "    *   `Dim_Product`\n",
      "        *   **Purpose:** Describes products and their categories.\n",
      "        *   **Columns:** `ProductKey` (PK, e.g., an integer ID), `Product`, `Category`.\n",
      "        *   **Key:** `ProductKey`\n",
      "    *   `Dim_Customer`\n",
      "        *   **Purpose:** Describes individual customers.\n",
      "        *   **Columns:** `CustomerID` (PK, original ID), `CustomerName` (if available, conceptual).\n",
      "        *   **Key:** `CustomerID`\n",
      "    *   `Dim_Region`\n",
      "        *   **Purpose:** Describes sales regions.\n",
      "        *   **Columns:** `RegionKey` (PK, e.g., an integer ID), `Region`.\n",
      "        *   **Key:** `RegionKey`\n",
      "    *   `Dim_Channel`\n",
      "        *   **Purpose:** Describes sales channels.\n",
      "        *   **Columns:** `ChannelKey` (PK, e.g., an integer ID), `Channel`.\n",
      "        *   **Key:** `ChannelKey`\n",
      "\n",
      "### 2.2 Core Measures (DAX Concepts)\n",
      "\n",
      "1.  **Total Sales Revenue**\n",
      "    *   **Meaning:** The grand total of money generated from all sales transactions.\n",
      "    *   **Calculation:** `SUM(Fact_Sales[SalesAmount])`\n",
      "    *   **Why it matters:** Primary financial performance indicator; shows overall business health.\n",
      "\n",
      "2.  **Total Quantity Sold**\n",
      "    *   **Meaning:** The total number of individual product units sold across all transactions.\n",
      "    *   **Calculation:** `SUM(Fact_Sales[Quantity])`\n",
      "    *   **Why it matters:** Indicates sales volume and product popularity; useful for inventory planning.\n",
      "\n",
      "3.  **Number of Unique Customers**\n",
      "    *   **Meaning:** The count of distinct customers who made at least one purchase.\n",
      "    *   **Calculation:** `DISTINCTCOUNT(Fact_Sales[CustomerID])`\n",
      "    *   **Why it matters:** Measures customer base engagement and reach.\n",
      "\n",
      "4.  **Average Order Value (AOV)**\n",
      "    *   **Meaning:** The average revenue generated per transaction.\n",
      "    *   **Calculation:** `[Total Sales Revenue] / COUNTROWS(Fact_Sales)`\n",
      "    *   **Why it matters:** Insights into customer spending habits; higher AOV usually means more efficient sales.\n",
      "\n",
      "5.  **Average Unit Price (Weighted)**\n",
      "    *   **Meaning:** The average price per unit sold, considering all transactions and quantities.\n",
      "    *   **Calculation:** `[Total Sales Revenue] / [Total Quantity Sold]`\n",
      "    *   **Why it matters:** Helps understand effective pricing and discount impacts across all sales.\n",
      "\n",
      "6.  **Total Discount Amount**\n",
      "    *   **Meaning:** The total monetary value of all discounts applied to sales.\n",
      "    *   **Calculation:** `SUMX(Fact_Sales, Fact_Sales[Quantity] * Fact_Sales[UnitPrice] * Fact_Sales[Discount])`\n",
      "    *   **Why it matters:** Measures the cost of discount strategies; crucial for profit margin analysis.\n",
      "\n",
      "7.  **Average Discount Rate**\n",
      "    *   **Meaning:** The average discount percentage applied across all sales.\n",
      "    *   **Calculation:** `[Total Discount Amount] / SUMX(Fact_Sales, Fact_Sales[Quantity] * Fact_Sales[UnitPrice])`\n",
      "    *   **Why it matters:** Evaluates the generosity or effectiveness of pricing and promotional strategies.\n",
      "\n",
      "8.  **Sales MoM Growth %**\n",
      "    *   **Meaning:** The percentage change in Total Sales Revenue from the previous month.\n",
      "    *   **Calculation:** Requires `CALCULATE([Total Sales Revenue], PREVIOUSMONTH(Dim_Date[Date]))` for previous month, then `DIVIDE(([Total Sales Revenue] - [Sales Previous Month]), [Sales Previous Month])`.\n",
      "    *   **Why it matters:** Tracks short-term sales momentum and identifies growth or decline trends.\n",
      "\n",
      "9.  **Sales YTD**\n",
      "    *   **Meaning:** Total Sales Revenue from the beginning of the year up to the current selected date.\n",
      "    *   **Calculation:** `CALCULATE([Total Sales Revenue], DATESYTD(Dim_Date[Date]))`\n",
      "    *   **Why it matters:** Provides cumulative performance view for a fiscal year.\n",
      "\n",
      "10. **Sales per Customer**\n",
      "    *   **Meaning:** Average revenue generated per unique customer.\n",
      "    *   **Calculation:** `[Total Sales Revenue] / [Number of Unique Customers]`\n",
      "    *   **Why it matters:** Helps in understanding customer lifetime value or segmenting customer profitability.\n",
      "\n",
